  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The goal of this study is to assess the effectiveness of vitamin D in reducing
      laboratory-confirmed influenza and in reducing non-influenza viral respiratory tract
      infections. A cohort of children between the ages of 3 and 17 years from the Thanh Ha
      Commune, Thanh Liem District, Ha Nam Province, Vietnam will be randomized to either weekly
      vitamin D supplements or placebo. Participants who develop acute respiratory infection over a
      12-month period, will be tested for influenza, the co-primary outcome, and other respiratory
      viruses, the other co-primary outcome, by RT-PCR.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
